explanations.reason: The paper focuses on the use of whole exome sequencing (WES) in the study of rare congenital ophthalmic diseases, specifically anterior segment dysgenesis (ASD). It discusses genomic research, molecular characterization, and the identification of genetic variants associated with ASD. There is no mention of any machine learning techniques, algorithms, or models in the title or abstract. The study is purely based on genomic and molecular biology techniques, not involving any computational or machine learning approaches.
